WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.840
First big Tai Chi movement, we are here and we do the noto-chordal wave.

2
00:00:06.220 --> 00:00:11.300
We bring it back with the entire mesodermal movement.

3
00:00:11.980 --> 00:00:17.420
The noto-chordal wave and below it, the entire mesodermal movement.

4
00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:19.620
Then, we focus on the brain.

5
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:24.720
1. Brain growth.

6
00:00:24.940 --> 00:00:27.040
2. Cephalic flexion.

7
00:00:28.062 --> 00:00:32.162
3. Cervical flexion.

8
00:00:33.922 --> 00:00:37.062
4. Pontic flexion.

9
00:00:40.062 --> 00:00:42.062
5. Telencephalization.

10
00:00:49.202 --> 00:00:54.262
Kidney movement. It's an exorotation movement.

11
00:00:58.825 --> 00:01:05.465
Now, we are going to do everything related to the bladder and uterus, and

12
00:01:05.465 --> 00:01:06.005
then we come back.

13
00:01:08.285 --> 00:01:10.025
Peritoneum, right hand in front.

14
00:01:11.225 --> 00:01:15.505
I take the loop here, I bring it towards my hepatic side.

15
00:01:15.845 --> 00:01:18.725
The hand here goes down and finishes the rotation like this.

16
00:01:20.285 --> 00:01:22.845
Like this, I have the loop here in front of me.

17
00:01:22.845 --> 00:01:24.065
It grows.

18
00:01:25.528 --> 00:01:30.568
I pull this hand, I come to get the loop here, I bring it towards

19
00:01:30.568 --> 00:01:31.068
my liver.

20
00:01:32.048 --> 00:01:37.168
And then the hand here goes down, goes up, and that one goes down to form the

21
00:01:37.168 --> 00:01:37.928
terminal phase.